    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-10-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Laird Brothers</persName> to <persName type="to">assistant collector of her Majesty’s customs,
                                    Liverpool</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Birkenhead Iron Works,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Birkenhead,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-10-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 8, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> We beg to acknowledge receipt of your
                                letter of this date, informing us that you have been directed to
                                place an officer on board the iron-clad vessel now nearest
                                completion, in the great float, Birkenhead, and that he has
                                directions to seize her in case any attempt be made to remove her
                                from where she is at present.</p>
                <p>We have given Mr. Morgan, the surveyor of customs, an order of
                                admission to the iron-clad (which is named the El Tousson) now lying
                                in the Birkenhead float, which order he will show to our watchman or
                                ship-keeper when going on board.</p>
                <p>We are, respectfully, your obedient servants,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>LAIRD BROTHERS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. G. Stewart,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">Assistant Collector of her Majesty’s Customs,
                                        Liverpool.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
